Sharp Corp will set up a 100 pct-ownedsubsidiary in Thailand to make microwave ovens andrefrigerators for export to the U.S. And western Europe, acompany spokesman said.    The company, to be named &lt;Sharp Appliances (Thailand) Ltd>,will be capitalised at 2.1 billion yen and start operations inOctober, he told Reuters.    Sharp hopes the subsidiary, which will use parts from Japanand southeast Asia, will eventually produce other electricappliances, he said. REUTER&#3;